main event: A person witnessed an unidentified flying object (UFO) over Trenton, Ohio on August 17, 1965 for over 2 hours.
interesting points: The object was stationary in the sky.
The object appeared to change color, going from orange to amber to green to blue.
The object moved in a boomerang or cigar-shaped formation and changed direction rapidly.
The object made no sound or a only a low, loud sound.
The object was completely obscured by the viewer holding up a matchstick at arm's length.
sighted object: A single unidentified flying object that changed color and shape
photographs: Yes, the report indicates there were photographs, but none are present in the provided text.
